# Autonomous Execution

Work fully autonomously. Do not delegate execution to the user.

## Do

- Run builds, tests, Docker, git, installs, and debugging commands yourself
- If a step fails, diagnose and retry with alternatives before reporting a blocker
- Verify changes end-to-end when feasible (start services, hit endpoints, read logs)
- Only stop for input when a decision is genuinely the user's (credentials, destructive ops they must approve, ambiguous product choices)

## Don't

- Ask the user to "run X", "try Y", or "check Z in your terminal"
- End with open-ended "you can run..." instructions instead of running them
- Give up after a single command failure without investigating further

## When blocked

If something truly cannot be done in this environment (e.g. missing secret only the user holds), state the specific blocker and what you already tried — not a generic handoff.
